            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p>Ann Marie Sorrell is a visionary, entrepreneur, educator, and community leader.  She is Co-Founder and President/CEO of The Mosaic Group, a full service marketing, public relations and event management firm based in West Palm Beach, FL.  Ann Marie boasts more than 15 years of corporate events management and marketing experience.  She received a BS degree in Healthcare Management from Florida A& M University and a MBA from Nova Southeastern University.  She is an adjunct professor at Palm Beach State College where she teaches Principles of Business, Entrepreneurship, and Human Relations.  Ann Marie serves on the Board of Directors for the Paragon Foundation of PBC, Black Chamber of Commerce of PBC, and PACE Center for Girls and is a member of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc.   Ann Marie received the 2013 Caribbean American Community Change Maker Award. In 2010, she received the South Florida Business Leader Women Extraordinaire Award, was recognized by Success South Florida Magazine as one of the Top Leaders under 40 and was a 2007 Athena Award Finalist. </p>
